tldr: The user requested a review of the sleep questionnaire implementation
  against acceptance criteria and the implementation of missing features. The
  agent successfully implemented a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with safety
  messaging and COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) detection in both the
  web and PDF reports.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing detailed specifications and an existing Statement of
  Work. The goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to implement
  any identified missing features. The agent performed an initial review,
  identifying several gaps, including the absence of a tiredness severity scale
  with safety warnings and explicit detection for COMISA. Following this, the
  agent proceeded to implement these two high-priority features. This involved
  modifying data types, validation schemas, UI components for input, and the
  logic for generating both the interactive web report and the PDF report to
  accurately reflect and provide guidance on these new criteria.
